              "id": "QUE59014",
              "question": "Which of the following examples best demonstrates a self-fulfilling stereotype?\n\u003cbr /\u003e",
              "order": "randomized",
              "presenterType": "RadioGroup",
              "presenterConfig": {
                "numberFormat": "none"
              },
              "choices": [
                {
                  "answerKey": "answer_1",
                  "content": "A student is told he has a severe learning disability. After researching how this disability may affect him, he begins unconsciously changing his habits and attitudes to conform to his own perceived expectations."
                },
                {
                  "answerKey": "answer_2",
                  "content": "A teenage girl is told that her boyfriend is cheating on her. She perceives him as a jerk and gives him the cold shoulder. Her behavior upsets him, and he breaks up with her."
                },
                {
                  "answerKey": "answer_3",
                  "content": "A math teacher hears that her new student is very smart and pleasant to work with. She gives him extra encouragement and challenging assignments. The student, who once did poorly in math and was surly in class, is now happy and cheerful and is willing to try more difficult work."
                },
                {
                  "answerKey": "answer_4",
                  "content": "Two women befriend another woman who is not a member of their social class. After getting to know her, they both change the way they perceive women from a lower social class."
                }
